The previously tracked 9 inconsistency items have been aligned in code:

1. Occupied-slot API naming aligned in shared API types/hook usage (`GetOccupiedTimeSlots*`).
2. Stale missing-route references removed from active contracts/interfaces.
3. `GET /api/history/getOccupiedTimeSlots` now enforces Clerk auth + role checks.
4. Dashboard user shape now uses `instantUser?.[0]?.id` consistently.
5. `POST /api/contract/update` and `POST /api/history/update` now validate status enums strictly.
6. `GET /api/history/getAll` pagination now returns `total` as full filtered count.
7. Contract date filters now apply to contract period fields (`start_date`, `end_date`) instead of `created_at`.
8. Legacy completion fallback removed; only `CHECKED_IN` is counted as completed.
9. Rulebook and main docs were refreshed to match current runtime behavior.

## 10) Change checklist for future modifications

When changing any page, API, status, role rule, data field, or design token, update in same PR:

- This file `.cursor/rules/gochul-fitness-rules.mdc`
- `src/app/type/api/index.ts`
- Affected API route handlers under `src/app/api/**`
- Relevant hooks under `src/hooks/**`
- Relevant UI pages/components under `src/app/(main)/**` and `src/components/**`
- `src/theme/colors.ts` when color or design-token behavior changes

Do not merge behavior changes without synchronized rulebook updates.
